article.headline: Oak Street Health's stock paces NYSE gainers on first day of trading
article.body: Shares of Oak Street Health Inc. OSH, -0.79% debuted with a bang Thursday, as they paced all NYSE percentage gainers on their first day of trading, after the initial public offering priced above its expected range. The Chicago-based network of primary care for adults raised about $328.1 million, after saying late Wednesday that it sold 15,625,000 shares in its IPO, which priced at $21 a share. The IPO was expected to price between $19 and $21 a share. At the IPO price, the company was valued at $5.01 billion. The stock's first trade was at $42.50, or 102.4% above the IPO price. It has pared some gains to be up 75% in afternoon trading. The company went public at a time that the Renaissance IPO ETF IPO, +1.98% has soared 48.4% over the past three months while the S&P 500 SPX, +0.87% has gained 17.5%.
